In the USINGZ build, stamp the z of vertices created on the join/split
paths. Upstream applies its z policy (SetZ: endpoint-coincident z with
subject priority, else DefaultZ, then the user callback) only where
IntersectEdges creates output points directly. Three call sites create
output points from an intersection point whose z GetLineIntersectPt left
as 0 and never invoke SetZ, so those vertices reach the output with z = 0
regardless of any registered callback or DefaultZ:

  - Split -> AddLocalMinPoly (joined edges split at an intersection)
  - CheckJoinLeft -> AddLocalMaxPoly
  - CheckJoinRight -> AddLocalMaxPoly

Apply SetZ to the returned OutPt at each site, mirroring the existing
IntersectEdges sites (nullptr-guarded where AddLocalMaxPoly can fail).
No behavior change without USINGZ, and none under USINGZ unless a
z callback is registered (SetZ returns early otherwise).

Found by fuzzing the cwrapper's z-sentinel contract; the related
DoSplitOp gap is handled in the wrapper's z callback (see sentinel_zcb
in cwrapper/cclipper2.cpp).

